<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Imgur Gallery</title><link>https://imgur.com</link><description>description</description><lastBuildDate>2022-05-09 14:11:56.316585</lastBuildDate><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qmgLpJH</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dcv9aRr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qmgLpJH</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ZipQuick]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Some people are still mothers</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/OShsvpz</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zgw1ngF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I went to lunch today to a Chinese buffet near my work. Since it was mothers day I decided I would pay for a moms meal secretly. I saw a lady mid 50s maybe early 60s. She looked sad thought maybe her kids stood her up for a mothers day lunch. So I paid for her lunch, and when the waitress went over and told her that her meal was already paid for and gave her a note I had wrote happy mothers day on to her. She began crying. Not just a how sweet cry but an ugly turn peoples heads ugly crying.
    I went over to the poor lady to see if she was ok. She looked at me oddly when I sat across from her at her table, and asked if she was alright. She opened up completely telling me her son had passed away last month after being hit by a drunk driver. Her and her son would come to this Chinese restaurant every Sunday to chat and spend time together. She had thought about not coming in today but she said she had a little voice tell her to do it that it would help her somehow. When the waitress told her that someone paid her meal she had a flash of her son. I sat with her a bit until she was able to calm down and she apologized for making such a scene and thanked me for listening. I told her that she had no need to apologize for grieving and that I hoped she would have a good day. She asked for a hug as we left and I gave her one and I swear it felt like a hug a mother would give her child. I felt so heart broken for her. 
    If you can remember to call her and say you love her. If you can see her do so and give her a hug. Have a happy mothers day Imgur.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/OShsvpz</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[retailmemedrone]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Neat</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/V4kJCdf</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/PjwknMh.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Her Etsy: https://etsy.me/3BhiTEP</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/V4kJCdf</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Yoda1PositivityStar]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>feels bad man</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/oRudIF9</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MV1BNyJ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/oRudIF9</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[roanhouse]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Basics..</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/ZdC71jB</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sAo8fIK.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/rK1PuIj.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NUOTLOX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/ZdC71jB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Srajo101]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Hope you had a great weekend!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/7XRnUb1</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Jto2Ilb.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/7XRnUb1</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SybilCrawley]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Can't trick mom!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/R