First photo taken before I checked into a facility for alcohol use and for my mental health.  The second is today.  25 days of no alcohol and new medication.  Clear skin, more energy, low blood pressure, healthy sleep schedule.  Feeling like a whole new person.  My mom doesn’t know about any of this but she told my husband after lunch today that she hasn’t seen me seeming so alive and alert in a long time.  Glad I could give her that for Mother’s Day.

IWNDWYT!

FP Edit: 
1. I really appreciate all the kind words and uplifting comments.  Love this community.
2. IWNDWYT is an acronym often used in support communities online.  It stands for “I will not drink with you today.”
3. I’ve had a couple of people comment about or shoot me messages re: recovery facilities.  I’m happy to answer any questions anyone has.  I did a lot of research going in and talked to a lot of people during my time who had been in a LOT of different facilities so while I can’t answer every question you might have, I can certainly answer many of them and am happy to share my personal experience as well.  

